text:
Set in the 1990s, Captain Marvel follows Danvers, an Air Force officer, as she becomes one of the universe's most powerful heroes after earth gets involved in a galactic war between alien. The film also stars Samuel L. Jackson, Ben Mendelsohn, and Jude Law.

Captain Marvel was released on March 8, 2019, and received generally positive reviews from critics, with many praising Larson's performance and the film's visual effects. It grossed over $1.1 billion at the box office, making it one of the highest-grossing films of 2019.

In 2023, a sequel titled The Marvels was released, which sees Danvers team up with Monica Rambeau (Teyonah Parris) and Kamala Khan (Iman Vellani).

### Avengers: Endgame (2019)

Main article: Avengers: Endgame

Avengers: Endgame is a superhero film directed by Anthony and Joe Russo and written by Christopher Markus and Stephen McFeely. The film follows the surviving members of the Avengers and their allies as they attempt to undo the damage caused by Thanos in the previous film.

The film features an ensemble cast, including Robert Downey Jr., Chris Evans, Mark Ruffalo, Chris Hemsworth, Scarlett Johansson, Jeremy Renner, and Brie Larson.

Avengers: Endgame was released on April 26, 2019, and received widespread critical acclaim, with praise for its epic scope, emotional weight, and satisfying conclusion to the Infinity Saga.
